# UI Components

## Constraints

- **Hierarchy:** Organize by `ui` (stateless primitives, Base UI-backed), `shared` (common, cross-feature), and `features/*` (domain logic).
- **Atomic:** Keep `src/components/ui` pure; forbid API/Store dependencies inside it.
- **Separation:** Separate data (container/feature) from UI (presentation/`ui`, `shared`).
- **Composition:** Prefer children-based composition over large prop objects.
- **Base UI Composition:** Base UI components are unstyled and compound (`Dialog.Root`, `Dialog.Trigger`, `Dialog.Popup`, ...). To make any element the trigger/anchor, use the `render` prop with a `ReactElement` â€” Base UI has no `asChild` (that is a Radix-only concept).
- **`Button` + `render`:** `@/ui` `Button` assumes it renders a native `<button>` (`nativeButton` defaults to `true`). When rendering it as a non-button element (`<a>`, `next/link`, `Dialog.Trigger`, ...) via the `render` prop, always pass `nativeButton={false}` â€” otherwise Base UI logs an accessibility warning.
- **Base UI Animation:** Animate open/close state via `data-[open]`, `data-[closed]`, `data-[starting-style]`, `data-[ending-style]` Tailwind arbitrary variants (see `dialog.tsx`, `tabs.tsx`). Do not reach for JS animation libraries for simple open/close transitions.
- **Variants:** Use `class-variance-authority` (`cva`) for components with visual variants (see `button.tsx`).
- **States:** Implement Skeleton (matching dimensions), EmptyState, and ErrorState for data-driven parts.
- **UX:** Avoid empty screens; always provide meaningful states.
- **Styling:** Use Tailwind CSS, `cn()`, and the design tokens defined in `src/styles/tailwind.css`. No hex/RGB or arbitrary values â€” use the Tailwind scale strictly.
- **A11y:** Enforce semantic HTML, `aria` attributes, and keyboard accessibility.
- **Exports:** Named exports only, re-exported through the folder's `index.ts` barrel.

## Bans

- **AI Aesthetic:** Default purple/indigo palettes, excessive gradients, overuse of `rounded-2xl`, generic card/grid layouts.
- **Magic Numbers:** Arbitrary values (e.g., `p-[13px]`); use Tailwind's spacing scale strictly.
- **UX/A11y:** `div` soup, "Lorem Ipsum", or `onClick` on non-interactive elements without keyboard support.
- **Logic:** Default exports or data fetching inside atomic (`ui`) components.
- **`asChild`:** Does not exist on Base UI. Use `render={<Element />}` instead.

## Correct Implementation

<example>
```tsx
export function Card({ title, children }: { title: string; children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <section className={cn("rounded-md border p-4 md:p-6")}>
      <h3 className="text-base font-semibold">{title}</h3>
      <div className="mt-4">{children}</div>
    </section>
  );
}
```
</example>

<example>
```tsx
<Dialog>
  <DialogTrigger render={<Button size="lg" />}>Open</DialogTrigger>
  <DialogContent>...</DialogContent>
</Dialog>
```
</example>

## Incorrect Implementation

<incorrect-example>
```tsx
export default function ActionButton({ label }: { label: string }) {
  return (
    <div
      style={{ backgroundColor: "#6366f1" }}
      className="rounded-2xl p-[11px] shadow-2xl"
      onClick={() => console.log("clicked")}
    >
      <span>{label}</span>
    </div>
  );
}
```
</incorrect-example>

